<br>
I for one am buying it cause it EXISTS! I think a post in a different topic said it perfectly when he said &quot;How would you like to run to the bathroom and see a sign that says Only for those have ordered the expansion.&quot; And the features OWN for a 35 mage such as myself, it almost feels as if they designed the entire expansion around people such as myself. We havent had a major content expansion like this for over 3 years and I am happy. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490410">Dalren Fieryblade of Tarew Marr</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=moonwyndwhyspers>Moonwynd Whyspers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(1/17/03 5:58:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8502.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I don't think we should buy LoY</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Fal and some of the other posters.<br>
<br>
Bank Space - Great feature...I HATE having to find people to help me transfer stuff to my mule.<br>
<br>
LFG Tool - Not sure what this is going to be...but Fal was right, class stereotype is the main issue.  Heck, when I go into PoD and shout LFG, I usually get passed by for a second or third tank.  I can deal out more DPS with my nukes and tanking pet than a second or third tank in a group can...AND the Cleric does not have to heal my pet...I take care of everything =)<br>
<br>
3. Guild management tool- This is very intriguing...and I do run a guild...so this alone may be worth the money.<br>
<br>
4. New content- I have never complained about new content yet.<br>
<br>
5. New race- Frogloks...you can take 'em or leave 'em...I might create one just for fun...<br>
<br>
6. Keeping EQ alive - I agree with Fal, Raz, and Jaytee.  <br>
<br>
Really, how much will you be put out by spending $18.00?  And to say that it doesn't matter what you look like...well, I can respect that if that's how you feel.  However, saying it doesn't matter what the mobs look like because you kill them in the same manner as every other mob??? Well, why not make them all look like round blobs of light...no real form or shape..no graphics at all.  Heck, why not just make EQ a text based MUD... (insert sarcasm here =)).<br>
<br>
I have put quite some time into EverQuest...a game I truly enjoy playing...with people I truly enjoy playing with.  I will spend the $18.00 and support EQ.  The designers and programmers may not get everything right...but we are all still here playing and for the most part, enjoying the game...so they have to be doing more right than they are wrong....and I look forward to these new features.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
<br>
